5.0 of 5 bubbles
Halong Bay and Victory Star Cruise
Oct 2012
Halong Bay is arguably one of the most beautiful places on earth. Huge (and not so huge) limestone rocks burst out of the sea. Cruise boats of all sizes and small local fishing boats coast among the huge rocks, quietly and gently - I don't remember one moment of the boat rocking. The water is warm and swimmable (a great relief after sweating for a week in humid Hanoi and environs). Lots of cruise boats of all sizes available. We were on the Victory Star - a luxury boat, very comfortable with great food, great service, great air conditioning and comfortable beds and lounge chairs. Spaceious and beautiful, it is a new boat (2000) that looks like an old boat - made of l beautiful dark wood (Vietnamese black walnut?), lovely large green plants on deck, I felt like I was in a 1930's or early 1940's movie and expected to see Sidney Greenstreet walk thru the door with Bogart and Bacall probably somewhere on deck. It was great fun and very relaxing after a week in Hanoi and environs. A great respite.
Written October 13, 2012
