Is Halong bay worth a 1 night luxury cruise?
Jul 2022 ‚Ä¢ Family
One thing for sure, Halong Bay is beautiful with its breathtaking scenery. However, is it worth the money to take a one night cruise on a luxury cruise? As a family we spent a while debating. The distance from Hanoi is fine - you leave around 8.30 and get to port around 11.30 (after a half hour stop at some Pearl and coffee tourist pitstop) and then take off in a mini boat to take you to your cruise boat - ours had 24 bedrooms. Don‚Äôt be disillusioned - yours is not the only boat in the bay! In fact there are loads of other lovely boats in your patch. In peak times we were told that there were 200 cruises in the whole of the unesco area spread over different sections. The smell of diesel fuel is quite overwhelming sometimes.
On board we were directed straight to the buffet which to be fair was quite good (tho not as good for pescatarians). What is hysterical is that it‚Äôs a bit bun fight like as the locals literally emptied the serving dish of prawns and clams. So don‚Äôt be all British and dilly dally when it comes to choosing what you want.
Then you head to your room and chill on your bed and balcony soaking up the majestic scenery. To be honest this was our favourite bit - it‚Äôs all beautiful and simple gorgeous watching the limestone world drift past you.
After that the cruise lines you up for things to do - trip through the caves, swimming, kayaking, fishing, happy hour, karaoke, breakfast, checkout, brunch and it seems like every hour there is an announcement over the tannoy.
In the evening there is a set dinner with about 6/7 courses - way too much food and actually it felt awkward not eating much of it due to fussiness. For me most of the courses were 6 or 7 out of 10 but there were a few courses that really weren‚Äôt suited to our pathetic western palates or pescies again. What was weird for us was that our family of 5 were almost the only westerners aboard - we were expecting a different probably more fun vibe on the boat. But obviously this will be different on different days.
The staff are well-trained, remembering your first names throughout. The male manager was very welcoming and spoke really good English. And Tam, the senior host was a delight.
So is it worth it? Our verdict was I hate to say it ‚Äònot really‚Äô (Obviously this is from our point of view so am sure lots of people love it). It‚Äôs expensive for one. We could have stayed in a really luxurious spa hotel for 3 nights for the same price. The cruise boats all go to their patch together, all moor together, all pretty much do the same thing, all queue up for the cave trip. It all feels a bit processed. In the evening we looked out and there was loads of litter floating around which was really sad and hopefully can be sorted.
If cruises are your thing - with buffet style food, organising reps and function rooms style hospitality then you will probably love it. The food wasn‚Äôt really our bag - too much and all a bit corporate. If you want to go, you might be better to take a day trip or we quite fancied the sea plane for an hour which I was told is a similar price. Or better still Ninh binh.
Written July 10, 2022
